'''Nicolas Seiwald''' (born 4 May 2001) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for {{German football updater|RBLeipzi}} club [[RB Leipzig]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|nicolas-seiwald/508736}}</ref>

==Club career==
Seiwald began his career in 2009 with the youth academy of [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]]. He made his professional debut playing for Red Bull Salzburg's [[Farm team#Association football|feeder team]], [[FC Liefering]], against [[WSG Swarovski Tirol|WSG Wattens]] on 24 May 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://soccerway.com/matches/2019/05/24/austria/1-liga/usk-anif/wsg-swarovski-wattens/2802883|title=Liefering vs. Swarovski Tirol|website=Soccerway|date=24 May 2019|access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref> He made his league debut on 21 November 2020 as a starter against [[SK Sturm Graz]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.salzburg24.at/sport/fussball/bundesliga/bundesliga-grazer-fegen-wie-ein-sturm-ueber-red-bull-salzburg-95907034|title=FC Red Bull Salzburg-SK Sturm|website=Salzburg24|date=22 November 2020|access-date=28 May 2021|language=de}}</ref> On 11 October 2022, Seiwald scored his first [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] goal in a 1–1 away draw against [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dinamo Zagreb 1–1 Salzburg|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2035697--dinamo-zagreb-vs-salzburg/|website=[[UEFA]]|date=11 October 2022}}</ref>

On 26 February 2023, Seiwald joined German side [[RB Leipzig]] for the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|2023–24 season]], signing a five-year contract with the club.<ref>{{Cite web|title=RB Leipzig verpflichtet Nicolas Seiwald|url=https://rbleipzig.com/de/news/2022-2023/rb-leipzig-verpflichtet-nicolas-seiwald/|website=RB Leipzig|date=26 February 2023|access-date=6 May 2023|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Fix: Seiwald wechselt im Sommer von RB Salzburg zu RB Leipzig|url=https://www.kicker.de/fix-seiwald-wechselt-im-sommer-von-rb-salzburg-zu-rb-leipzig-939485/artikel|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|date=26 February 2023|access-date=6 May 2023|language=de}}</ref>

==International career==
Having represented [[Austria national football team|Austria]] at various youth levels,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://wiki.salzburg12.at/Nicolas_Seiwald|title=Nicolas Seiwald|website=FC Salzburg Wiki|access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref> Seiwald debuted for [[Austria national football team]] on 12 November 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group F|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Israel national football team|Israel]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Thomas|last=Gottsmann|title=WM-Qualifikation: Österreich schlägt Israel 4:2 - Joker Schaub sichert Fodas Job|url=https://www.sn.at/sport/fussball/nationalteam/video-wm-qualifikation-oesterreich-schlaegt-israel-42-joker-schaub-sichert-fodas-job-112177057|website=[[Salzburger Nachrichten]]|date=12 November 2021|language=de|quote=Debütant Nicolas Seiwald fälschte einen harmlosen Freistoß von Nir Bitton mit der Hand ins eigene Tor ab  0–1.|trans-quote=Debutant Nicolas Seiwald deflected a harmless free kick from Nir Bitton into his own goal.}}</ref>

